---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Docs — Hal" description="Get started with Hal: install, configure, and run your first autonomous coding loop.">
  <style>
    .container {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 24px;
    }
    .doc-header {
      padding: 64px 0 24px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .doc-header h1 {
      font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px);
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -1.2px;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .doc-header p {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .doc-body h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.4px;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin: 40px 0 12px;
    }
    .doc-body h3 {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin: 28px 0 8px;
    }
    .doc-body p {
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .doc-body a {
      color: var(--accent-hover);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .doc-body pre {
      background: var(--bg-surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 14px 18px;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 12px 0;
    }
    .doc-body code {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .doc-body ul, .doc-body ol {
      margin: 8px 0 16px 20px;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .doc-body li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .doc-footer {
      margin-top: 48px;
      padding: 24px 0 64px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .doc-footer a {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      transition: color 0.2s ease;
    }
    .doc-footer a:hover {
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="doc-header">
      <h1>Documentation</h1>
      <p>Install, configure, and run your first autonomous coding loop.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-body">
      <h2>Installation</h2>
      <p>Run the install script from your terminal:</p>
      <pre>curl -fsSL https://hal.run/install.sh | bash</pre>
      <p>This downloads the latest release, links the <code>hal</code> binary into your <code>PATH</code>, and creates a default config directory at <code>~/.hal/</code>.</p>

      <h2>Quick start</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Initialize</strong> a project:
          <pre>hal init</pre>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Plan</strong> a feature:
          <pre>hal plan "add user authentication"</pre>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Run</strong> the loop:
          <pre>hal run</pre>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>Hal will generate a PRD, convert it to stories, validate them, then implement and commit each one until the feature ships.</p>

      <h2>Core commands</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>hal init</code> — Create <code>.hal/</code> config and templates in the current repo.</li>
        <li><code>hal plan "description"</code> — Generate a PRD with user stories.</li>
        <li><code>hal convert</code> — Transform the PRD into structured JSON.</li>
        <li><code>hal validate</code> — Check every story against quality rules.</li>
        <li><code>hal run</code> — Execute the full loop: plan → convert → validate → ship.</li>
        <li><code>hal archive</code> — Save the current loop state so you can switch features.</li>
        <li><code>hal restore</code> — Bring back a previously archived loop.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Configuration</h2>
      <p>After <code>hal init</code>, edit <code>.hal/config.yaml</code> to set your preferred agent engine and project standards:</p>
      <pre>engine: claude-code
standards:
  - .hal/standards/typescript.md
  - .hal/standards/testing.md</pre>
      <p>Supported engines: <code>claude-code</code>, <code>openai-codex</code>, <code>pi</code>.</p>

      <h2>Next steps</h2>
      <p>Read the full README on GitHub for advanced topics: custom standards, engine plugins, CI integration, and troubleshooting.</p>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/j-yw/hal#readme" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View README on GitHub →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-footer">
      <a href="/">← Back to home</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/j-yw/hal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
